There are 729 commutative ternary operators (3**(sum(1..3))) vs 8 binary ones (2**(sum(1..2)))

There are 27 unary ternary operators (3**3) vs 4 binary ones (2**2)

^^^ tru yields TRUe
000 zer yields ZERo
vvv fls yields FaLSe

v^0 inc INCrement
^0v sam SAMe as input
0v^ dec DECrement

^v0 tpv PiVot around True
v0^ upv PIVot around unknown (not)
0^v fpv PiVot around False (ofa)

^vv ist IS True
v^v isu IS Unknown (unk)
vv^ isf IS False

v^^ nit Not Is True
^v^ niu Not Is Unknown (kno)
^^v nif Not Is False

^00 tor will be True when ORed with something else
v00 uor will be Unknown when ORed with something else
vv0 for will be False when ORed with something else

0vv tan will be True when ANded with something else
00v uan will be Unknown when ANded with something else
00^ fan will be False when ANded with something else

^^0 ofo
^0^
0^^ ota

